title: FORD STARTIME -- a 1960 episode directed by Alfred Hitchcock
description:
"Incident at a Corner" with Vera Miles, George Peppard, Paul Hartman, 
Jack Albertson, Bob Sweeney, and Joe Flynn.

Ford Startime was a dramatic anthology series originally aired on NBC during the entire 1959 to 1960 season, and was produced in color. Some episodes were produced by Hubbell Robinson. One by Jerry Lewis ( his remake of "The Jazz Singer" previously uploaded ). This is the only one from Alfred Hitchcock's production company and he also directed it. Although this appears to be a DVD copy the Ford Motors opening theme was removed, but it's complete other than that.
